    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="949"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d949">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5611/7–654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy United States Representative at the United
                        Nations</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WADSWORTHJJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-06">July 6,
                            1954</date>.<lb/>Received 11: 36 p.m.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. Reference Marshallese petition. US trusteeship delegation was today shown by
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Secretariat copy of draft resolution
                    submitted by <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss> on Marshallese petition and
                    given informal translation of Russian text. Main points as follows: <pb
                        facs="1535" n="1507" xml:id="pg_1507"/>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Preamble declares <gloss target="#t_Hndashbomb1">H-bomb</gloss>
                            experiments in trust territory inconsistent with <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                                >UN</gloss> charter, especially Article 83 (2), and with trusteeship
                            agreement and US obligations under trusteeship system.</p>
                        <p>Operative paragraphs recommend that: <list>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                <item>US stop tests in trust territory.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Provide full compensation to those affected by recent
                                    tests.</item>
                                <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                <item>Restore full rights of inhabitants to all land used for
                                    tests.</item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Resolution will be circulated tomorrow morning as document <gloss target="#t_TC1"
                        >TC</gloss>/.2/<gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss>.101.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WADSWORTHJJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
